summary: An Ordinance authorizing the Mayor and City Comptroller to issue Local Improvement Bonds for the improvement of East Olive Street, from Thirty-seventh Avenue to Fortieth Avenue et al, in the City of Seattle, by grading and constructing wooden curbs and gutters under Ordinance No. 14986, creating Local Improvement District No. 1340 prescribing the rate of interest thereon and authorizing their delivery to the contractor constructing the improvement.
